				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Google Researches Alternative Authentication Methods
				</h2>
				

						
						
							
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1769641">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Elasto</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1769626#post1769626" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">I had started to get to the point that I had a draft email with password hints to myself for the various sites. Part of the problem is some sites, when you forget your password and trigger a reset, won't allow you to use a password you've used before. So I slowly but inevitably get 'password drift/fragmentation' over time - which only gets worse as the number of passwords I have in active use grows.<br />
